main event: Observers reported seeing approximately seven to ten disc-shaped objects flying west at a very high speed near Milwaukee, Wisconsin on June 23, 1947.
interesting points: The objects were described as disc-shaped and appeared to move at a high rate of speed,The sighting lasted for over 10 minutes,This incident coincided with a period of heightened public interest in flying saucer reports,The objects were compared to 'pie plates' by some witnesses,The conclusion drawn was insufficient data for evaluation.
witness description: The observer's details are incomplete, but a lieutenant was noted.
